18template <typename Char, typename Base>
19class SimpleStringResource : public Base {
20 public:
21 // Takes ownership of |data|.
22 SimpleStringResource(Char* data, size_t length)
23 : data_(data),
24 length_(length) {}
25
26 ~SimpleStringResource() override { delete[] data_; }
27
28 const Char* data() const override { return data_; }
29
30 size_t length() const override { return length_; }
31
32 private:
33 Char* const data_;
34 const size_t length_;
35};
36
37using SimpleOneByteStringResource =
38 SimpleStringResource<char, v8::String::ExternalOneByteStringResource>;
39using SimpleTwoByteStringResource =
40 SimpleStringResource<base::uc16, v8::String::ExternalStringResource>;
41
42static constexpr int kMinOneByteLength =
43 kExternalPointerSlotSize - kTaggedSize + 1;
44static constexpr int kMinTwoByteLength =
45 (kExternalPointerSlotSize - kTaggedSize) / sizeof(base::uc16) + 1;
46static constexpr int kMinOneByteCachedLength =
47 2 * kExternalPointerSlotSize - kTaggedSize + 1;
48static constexpr int kMinTwoByteCachedLength =
49 (2 * kExternalPointerSlotSize - kTaggedSize) / sizeof(base::uc16) + 1;
50
51// static
52const char* ExternalizeStringExtension::BuildSource(char* buf, size_t size) {
53 base::SNPrintF(base::Vector<char>(buf, static_cast<int>(size)),
54 "native function externalizeString();"
55 "native function createExternalizableString();"
56 "native function isOneByteString();"
57 "let kExternalStringMinOneByteLength = %d;"
58 "let kExternalStringMinTwoByteLength = %d;"
59 "let kExternalStringMinOneByteCachedLength = %d;"
60 "let kExternalStringMinTwoByteCachedLength = %d;",
61 kMinOneByteLength, kMinTwoByteLength, kMinOneByteCachedLength,
62 kMinTwoByteCachedLength);
63 return buf;
64}
65v8::Local<v8::FunctionTemplate>
66ExternalizeStringExtension::GetNativeFunctionTemplate(
67 v8::Isolate* isolate, v8::Local<v8::String> str) {
68 if (strcmp(*v8::String::Utf8Value(isolate, str), "externalizeString") == 0) {
69 return v8::FunctionTemplate::New(isolate,
70 ExternalizeStringExtension::Externalize);
71 } else if (strcmp(*v8::String::Utf8Value(isolate, str),
72 "createExternalizableString") == 0) {
73 return v8::FunctionTemplate::New(
74 isolate, ExternalizeStringExtension::CreateExternalizableString);
75 } else {
76 DCHECK_EQ(strcmp(*v8::String::Utf8Value(isolate, str), "isOneByteString"),
77 0);
78 return v8::FunctionTemplate::New(isolate,
79 ExternalizeStringExtension::IsOneByte);
80 }
81}

85bool HasExternalForwardingIndex(Handle<String> string) {
86 if (!string->IsShared()) return false;
87 uint32_t raw_hash = string->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
88 return Name::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash);
89}

93void ExternalizeStringExtension::Externalize(
94 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
95 DCHECK(ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
96 if (info.Length() < 1 || !info[0]->IsString()) {
97 info.GetIsolate()->ThrowError(
98 "First parameter to externalizeString() must be a string.");
99 return;
100 }
101 bool result = false;
102 Handle<String> string = Utils::OpenHandle(*info[0].As<v8::String>());
103 const bool externalize_as_one_byte = string->IsOneByteRepresentation();
104 if (!string->SupportsExternalization(
105 externalize_as_one_byte ? v8::String::Encoding::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING
106 : v8::String::Encoding::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING)) {
107 // If the string is shared, testing with the combination of
108 // --shared-string-table and --isolate in d8 may result in races to
109 // externalize the same string. If GC is stressed in addition, this test
110 // might fail as the string was already externalized (marked for
111 // externalization by another thread and externalized during GC).
112 if (!StringShape(*string).IsExternal()) {
113 info.GetIsolate()->ThrowError("string does not support externalization.");
114 }
115 return;
116 }
117 if (externalize_as_one_byte) {
118 uint8_t* data = new uint8_t[string->length()];
119 String::WriteToFlat(*string, data, 0, string->length());
120 SimpleOneByteStringResource* resource = new SimpleOneByteStringResource(
121 reinterpret_cast<char*>(data), string->length());
122 result = Utils::ToLocal(string)->MakeExternal(resource);
123 if (!result) delete resource;
124 } else {
125 base::uc16* data = new base::uc16[string->length()];
126 String::WriteToFlat(*string, data, 0, string->length());
127 SimpleTwoByteStringResource* resource = new SimpleTwoByteStringResource(
128 data, string->length());
129 result = Utils::ToLocal(string)->MakeExternal(resource);
130 if (!result) delete resource;
131 }
132 // If the string is shared, testing with the combination of
133 // --shared-string-table and --isolate in d8 may result in races to
134 // externalize the same string. Those races manifest as externalization
135 // sometimes failing if another thread won and already forwarded the string to
136 // the external resource. Don't consider those races as failures.
137 if (!result && !HasExternalForwardingIndex(string)) {
138 info.GetIsolate()->ThrowError("externalizeString() failed.");
139 return;
140 }
141}

145MaybeHandle<String> CopyConsStringToOld(Isolate* isolate,
146 Handle<ConsString> string) {
147 return isolate->factory()->NewConsString(handle(string->first(), isolate),
148 handle(string->second(), isolate),
149 AllocationType::kOld);
150}

154void ExternalizeStringExtension::CreateExternalizableString(
155 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
156 DCHECK(ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
157 if (info.Length() < 1 || !info[0]->IsString()) {
158 info.GetIsolate()->ThrowError(
159 "First parameter to createExternalizableString() must be a string.");
160 return;
161 }
162 Handle<String> string = Utils::OpenHandle(*info[0].As<v8::String>());
163 Isolate* isolate = reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
164 v8::String::Encoding encoding = string->IsOneByteRepresentation()
165 ? v8::String::Encoding::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING
166 : v8::String::Encoding::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
167 if (string->SupportsExternalization(encoding)) {
168 info.GetReturnValue().Set(Utils::ToLocal(string));
169 return;
170 }
171 // Return the string if it is already externalized.
172 if (StringShape(*string).IsExternal()) {
173 info.GetReturnValue().Set(Utils::ToLocal(string));
174 return;
175 }
176
177 // Read-only strings are never externalizable. Don't try to copy them as
178 // some parts of the code might rely on some strings being in RO space (i.e.
179 // empty string).
180 if (IsReadOnlyHeapObject(*string)) {
181 info.GetIsolate()->ThrowError("Read-only strings cannot be externalized.");
182 return;
183 }
184#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
185 // Small strings may not be in-place externalizable.
186 if (string->Size() < static_cast<int>(sizeof(UncachedExternalString))) {
187 info.GetIsolate()->ThrowError("String is too short to be externalized.");
188 return;
189 }
190#endif
191
192 // Special handling for ConsStrings, as the ConsString -> ExternalString
193 // migration is special for GC (Tagged pointers to Untagged pointers).
194 // Skip if the ConsString is flat (second is empty), as we won't be guaranteed
195 // a string in old space in that case.
196 if (IsConsString(*string, isolate) && !string->IsFlat()) {
197 Handle<String> result;
198 if (CopyConsStringToOld(isolate, Handle<ConsString>::cast(string))
199 .ToHandle(&result)) {
200 DCHECK(result->SupportsExternalization(encoding));
201 info.GetReturnValue().Set(Utils::ToLocal(result));
202 return;
203 }
204 }
205 // All other strings can be implicitly flattened.
206 if (encoding == v8::String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING) {
207 MaybeHandle<SeqOneByteString> maybe_result =
208 isolate->factory()->NewRawOneByteString(string->length(),
209 AllocationType::kOld);
210 Handle<SeqOneByteString> result;
211 if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
212 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
213 String::WriteToFlat(*string, result->GetChars(no_gc), 0,
214 string->length());
215 DCHECK(result->SupportsExternalization(encoding));
216 info.GetReturnValue().Set(Utils::ToLocal(Handle<String>::cast(result)));
217 return;
218 }
219 } else {
220 MaybeHandle<SeqTwoByteString> maybe_result =
221 isolate->factory()->NewRawTwoByteString(string->length(),
222 AllocationType::kOld);
223 Handle<SeqTwoByteString> result;
224 if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
225 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
226 String::WriteToFlat(*string, result->GetChars(no_gc), 0,
227 string->length());
228 DCHECK(result->SupportsExternalization(encoding));
229 info.GetReturnValue().Set(Utils::ToLocal(Handle<String>::cast(result)));
230 return;
231 }
232 }
233 info.GetIsolate()->ThrowError("Unable to create string");
234}

236void ExternalizeStringExtension::IsOneByte(
237 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
238 DCHECK(ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
239 if (info.Length() != 1 || !info[0]->IsString()) {
240 info.GetIsolate()->ThrowError(
241 "isOneByteString() requires a single string argument.");
242 return;
243 }
244 bool is_one_byte = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*info[0].As<v8::String>())
245 ->IsOneByteRepresentation();
246 info.GetReturnValue().Set(is_one_byte);
247}
